foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: *Although DOI indicated in its FY 2010 Annual Report that there were 1200 requests overall pending at the end of the fiscal year, the figures in this chart are more accurate. The differences between this chart and the one in last year’s report are attributed to the following: 1) in some cases, the bureau/office did not update the EFTS to reflect that some requests were in fact completed or closed during previous years (as far back as FY 2007) until FY 2011; and 2) some requests that were received in FY 2010 were not entered in the EFTS until FY 2011 due to changes in personnel or human error.

foia:ProcessedResponseTimeSection.foia:FootnoteText:
(1) All charts that report Median and Average processing times for the “Agency Overall” do not include OIG data. OIG uses its own electronic request tracking system and also continues to manually track a number of its oldest requests.
(2) DOI employs four request processing tracks: Simple, Normal, Complex and Expedited. (The Normal track is for requests that can be processed within 20 workdays.) For purposes of appropriate charts in Section VII (A), (B), (C) and (D) of this report, data for the Normal and Complex tracks were combined for all bureaus (except OIG) to produce statistics for Median/Average/Lowest/Highest number of days.

foia:ProcessedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: Although some of these statistics differ from the numbers contained in DOI’s FY 2010 Annual Report, the figures in this chart are believed to be more accurate. The differences between this chart and the one in last year’s report are attributed to the following: 1) in some cases, the bureau/office did not update the EFTS to reflect that some requests were in fact processed during the previous year until now; and 2) some requests received in FY 2010 were not entered in the EFTS until FY 2011 due to changes in personnel or human error.
